      "type": "html",
      "text": " <i>Translation is a non-issue. I listed no constraints on the language in which the summary is provided, nor on the amount of translation between one system and another (so long as that translation has a well-defined lossiness... ideally zero). Obviously, the party receiving the summary must be able to read the summary (which may require that translation) because a summary only can only ever <b>prove understanding</b> to those intelligences that can both read and test it. In practice, that means the tester must have an equal or better education in the subject matter and jargon involved as does the testee. That doesn't change simply because we're talking about AIs.</i>",
